					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment.</support>
								<extent>182 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>145</height>
										<width>100</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>95/90</height>
										<width>60/55</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>182 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>18 quires: i-xii10 (folios 1-120), xiii8 (folios 121-128), xiv10 (folios 129-138), xv12 (folios 139-150), xvi-xvii10 (folios 151-170), xviii14-2 (folios 171-182). </p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quires.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="16" writtenLines="16">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Visible plummet ruling.</p>
									<p>Initial words written in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side are indistinguishable.</p>
									<p>Gilt edges. </p>
									<p>Erasures by censors (e. g. folios 10r, 24v, 25r, 31r, 94r, 135v).</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive, Ashkenazi and Provencal square script, punctuated. <name type="person" role="scribe">Daniyel ben Yitsḥaḳ of Ventura</name> (folios 1-143) and <name type="person" role="scribe">Avraham Farissol</name> (folios 144-182).</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="scribe">Daniyel ben Yitsḥaḳ of Ventura</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, <name type="place">Bologna</name>, <date calendar="Hebrew">[5]261</date> [<date calendar="Gregorian">1501</date>] (folio 140r); the word Daniel is decorated (folio 72v).
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="scribe">Avraham Farissol</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, <date calendar="Hebrew">[5]262</date> [<date calendar="Gregorian">1502</date>] (folio 182v).
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="patron">Daṿid Marḳ of Cine bar Avraham</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon upon the erased name of the patron (folio 182v).
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Riḳah</name>, the sister of Daniyel ben Yitsḥaḳ of Ventura, wife of Eli῾ezer of Rovigo, first owner: inscribed with her name in the colophon, <name type="place">Bologna</name>, <date calendar="Hebrew">[5]261</date> [<date calendar="Gregorian">1501</date>] (folio 140r).
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Dominico Irosolimitano</name> (fl. 1585-1624): inscribed with his name (folio 182v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">62-74</ref>.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Ivory leather.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Siddur. Roman Use. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27,029.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
